Hi FinTrack Ops Team,

Escalated this to Engineering. The root cause was a stuck job in the export queue caused by a worker node restart during a routine deployment (per our internal Deployment Runbook, canary deployments can occasionally strand queued jobs if they land on a node being cycled out). Your export job was orphaned rather than requeued automatically — this is a bug we're filing internally.

Engineering manually re-queued exp_9931f2 and it's now processing; given the size of your historical dataset (proj_71144 spans 3 years of data across our hot/warm/cold storage tiers described in our System Architecture Overview), full completion is estimated at 4-5 hours. You'll receive an email with a signed download link when it completes.

Given your Friday deadline, I've also flagged this as priority in our export processing queue so it won't be deprioritized behind other jobs.

We'll follow up once it completes.

Best,
